dct_description_sm: Printed with vegetation. Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (AM), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , original map compiled by USGS. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Indianapolis West, Indiana : Marion County. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3763 I SW. AMS 1. "A.M.S. series , V851" "Transverse Mercator projection." Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "Contour interval 10 feet." Marginal maps: Index to boundaries.--Index to adjoining sheets. "Scale changed, marginal data revised and Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, 1948. Copied 1948 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Indianapolis East, 1948. Original map compiled by USGS from planetable surveys and stereophotogrammetric methods, 1946. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS. ... Map field checked." "N3945-W8607.5/7.5." "7-48."
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, 1948.
